\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.7 Closure Standards
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The assigned technician shall not close a work order until the work is complete,
 the resolution is documented,
 and the appropriate closure status has been applied in accordance with work order operational standards maintained in the System of Engagement.
 The terminal closure state for confirmed,
 properly completed work is Resolution Confirmed,
 as defined in the System of Engagement.
 Resolution Confirmed seals the work order record.
 Any future work on the same asset or issue requires a new work order.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Prior to applying any closed status,
 the assigned technician shall ensure that:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
All actions taken are documented in the Notes section.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The resolution or disposition is stated clearly and completely.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Applicable assets are linked via the Related Issues field.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The user has been notified of the closure or disposition in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Where user confirmation is required,
 the Reached for Confirmation checkbox has been applied and the user's response documented.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
