\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.8 Emergency Exception
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
When an operational emergency requires immediate IT action before a work order can be created,
 the responding Information Operations Personnel may proceed with emergency action prior to work order creation.
 This exception is narrow.
 It applies only when the time required to create a work order before acting would materially extend the duration or severity of the impact.
 It does not represent a general relaxation of the work order requirement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The emergency exception suspends the sequence;
 it does not eliminate the requirement.
 The responding Information Operations Personnel shall create a work order as soon as operationally practicable and in all cases no later than one (1) business hour following the initiation of emergency action or the conclusion of the immediate emergency phase,
 whichever is earlier.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The responding Information Operations Personnel shall document the following in work orders created under this exception:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The nature of the emergency and the specific conditions that justified bypassing standard work order creation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
All actions taken prior to work order creation,
 with the most precise timestamps recoverable.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
A notation in the work order that the emergency exception was invoked.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall acknowledge the emergency exception work order within one (1) business day of its creation by entering an acknowledgment notation in the work order.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The assigned technician shall apply the On-Call checkbox defined in the System of Engagement to all work orders created in connection with after-hours emergency response for statistical tracking purposes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall review emergency exception work orders in aggregate no less than quarterly.
 The quarterly review shall examine the frequency of emergency exception invocations,
 the consistency of catch-up work order creation with the one (1) business hour requirement,
 the adequacy of documented justifications,
 and whether patterns indicate systemic conditions warranting process improvement rather than continued exception use.
 The IT Director shall document review findings and any resulting corrective actions in the System of Engagement.
 Patterns of emergency exception usage inconsistent with the narrow criteria defined above shall be addressed as a compliance matter under 
\series bold
Policy 
